==Trivia==
[[File:Ant Man Test Footage 2.jpg|thumb|250px|Ant-Man concept still]]
*In the comics, Scott Lang is the second individual to take up the Ant-Man mantle with the approval of [[Hank Pym]], after he originally steals the [[Ant-Man Suit]] in order to take care of his daughter [[Cassie Lang|Cassandra]]'s medical bills. He also had a relationship with [[Jessica Jones]] with Jessica's best friend [[Carol Danvers]] acting as their matchmaker.
**His Giant-Man persona doesn't exist in the Earth-616 (mainstream) continuity, but rather on Earth-1610, the ''Ultimates'' comics. Here, Lang never became Ant-Man, but inherits from [[Hank Pym]] the title of Giant-Man, a super-soldier working for [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]
*Scott Lang is the first character in the Marvel Cinematic Universe to have taken over the mantle of a former superhero, followed by [[Robbie Reyes]], [[Hope van Dyne]] and [[Sam Wilson]].
*Ant-Man is one of the three heroes, to have defeated the main antagonist of their first standalone movie without any assistance, the other two being [[Hulk]] and [[Spider-Man]].
*Scott Lang is a fan of the baseball team, the {{WPS|San Francisco Giants}}.{{Ref|LOftLG}}

==Behind the Scenes==
*Before [[Paul Rudd]] was cast as Ant-Man, {{WPS|Adrien Brody}}, {{WPS|Joseph Gordon-Levitt}}, {{WPS|Simon Pegg}} and {{WPS|Ewan McGregor}} were all in the running for the role.
*[[Colin Follenweider]], [[Mark Wagner]], [[Brett Smrz]], [[Marlow Warrington-Mattei]] and [[James Harris]] were stunt doubles for [[Paul Rudd]] in the role of Ant-Man.
*[[Michael Aaron Milligan]], [[Brian Simpson]] and [[Kevin Marshall]] were stand-ins for [[Paul Rudd]] in the role of Ant-Man.
*According to [[Andy Park]], in the early stages of development of ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'', Lang was meant to side with [[Iron Man]] during the [[Avengers Civil War]], like [[Hank Pym]] in the original ''Civil War'' comic book storyline. This was later changed as the script evolved.<ref>[https://www.screengeek.net/2016/08/24/civil-war-concept-art-reveals-iron-man-team-almost-featured-ant-man-giant-man/ Civil War Concept Art Reveals Iron Man’s Team Almost Featured GIANT MAN/ANT-MAN]</ref>
**Screenwriters [[Christopher Markus]] and [[Stephen McFeely]] later revealed that had [[Sony Pictures Entertainment|Sony]] declined [[Marvel Studios]] the use of [[Spider-Man]], Lang would have been on the opposite team.<ref>[https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2436710/ant-man-almost-ended-up-on-team-iron-man-in-captain-america-civil-war Why Ant-Man Was Originally Team Iron Man In Captain America: Civil War]</ref>

